"Into a pint glass, pours a semi-hazy gold, with a nice one inch head that settles to film, and good lacing. The aroma is pretty tame, some decent wheat malt, some lemon, maybe some clove, not much else. The taste get a bit funky, but still pretty good. Some wheat malt, some citrus, some clove, maybe a funky bit of yeast is what I was getting at first. The mouth is decent, body isn't half bad, carbonation is decent, drying a bit at end. In all, not a bad brew, but rubs me wrong for whatever reason."
"Mouthfeel is smooth and easy drinking with a mix between crispness and creaminess. Pretty much spot on for the style. Overall, it would be easy to drink a good deal of this and would go well on a hot day on a nude beach (although they need to can this brew as you can't bring bottles on the nude beach!!)"
"This is a really light offering. Pretty wimpy beer with very little character whatsoever. No off tastes, but very little to get excited about here. I guess it would be okay out in the boat on a hot day. But it was pretty unsatisfying. Compared to a 312 or a Spotted Cow, it is just lame. Wimpy, wimpy, wimpy."
"A very drinkable, very satisfying summer brew."
