"Poured into a pint glass this brew is a decent orange, brownish amber color with a 1/2 white head that dissipated quickly leaving a slight cap. The smell is moderately citrus with a hint of malt. The flavor is a little less than expected. There is noticeable wheat taste with mild hints of citrus and some slight spice in the background. The carbonation is good opening some flavors up in the after taste. Not over the top great, but this is a nice addition to the Point arsenal."
" ~ This is a solid brew that I'll recommend to friends. On a side note, it's nice to see the Point Brewery dabbling in different beers and extending their beer selection."
